cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.IR 

This paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category as it deals with image segmentation. The use of neural networks for the merging priorities estimator suggests that it could also belong to the machine learning (cs.LG) sub-category. Additionally, the paper involves training the watershed computation jointly with boundary map prediction, which could fall under the artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-category. The recurrent neural network used for learning complex shape priors could also suggest the neural networks (cs.NE) sub-category. Finally, the paper could also be relevant to the information retrieval (cs.IR) sub-category as it deals with image analysis and segmentation.
